<p>I have button which expands\collapses content and according to this state I want to change chevron glyph to up chevron or down chevron <a href="http://prntscr.com/8mgs7i" rel="nofollow">like this</a> In my xaml I use binding to bool property which indicates current state and use converter which returns proper code for chevron:</p>  <pre><code> &lt;FontIcon Style="{StaticResource GlyphIconTextStyle}"                           Margin="0 0 5 0"                           Glyph="{x:Bind ViewModel.IsExpanded, Converter={StaticResource VerticalChevronConverter}}"/&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Here is code of my converter:</p>  <pre><code>public class VerticalChevronConverter : IValueConverter {     public object Convert(object value, Type targetType, object parameter, string language)     {         var boolValue = (bool)value;          if (boolValue)         return "&amp;#xE96E;";          return "&amp;#xE96D;";     }      public object ConvertBack(object value, Type targetType, object parameter, string language)     {         throw new NotImplementedException();     } } </code></pre>  <p>As a result I see <a href="http://prntscr.com/8mgtkw" rel="nofollow">this</a> in my app</p>  <p>Please help how to implement this switch</p>